<br>
I'm already frigging wasting my mana and raid time and in many cases my own pearls to coth people, and I hate having to bug people to go be coth inviters.  <br>
<br>
Listen.. <br>
<br>
I CAN'T SET UP A COTH GROUP FOR YOU!  Someone else invites me, then goes to invite you.  All I do is sit here and press alt-3 when you're ready.  Ask someone in charge at the raid.  If you want, ask me about the coth situation, of course I'll probably be the one involved, so I can tell you about the raid situation, but don't expect me to do all your work for you.<br>
<br>
What you need to do to get a coth is to find someone currently with me that can get to you.  It would help a lot if you need to show up late to a raid where a coth group is not currently set up to organize it yourself.  Ask for someone to come get you and have them invite me.  Sure, I'll be happy to coth you in, just don't make me bother other people.  You're the one late for the raid, that's your job.<br>
<br>
/sigh.  I know most reading this are probably coth mages anyway... I was just pissed and felt like ranting <p><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE><center><b>Goladus Mistrydia</b></font><br>
